nodes.title: Tip
widgets_values:
Copy paste the path to the image sequence. In this case, it is sufficient to only past the path to the folder, you dont need to add the file.
Like this:

path\to\comfyUI\ComfyUI_windows_portable\ComfyUI\output\save_upscale_images_57\sampling_iterations

nodes.title: Tip:
widgets_values:
Always set the sample count to a multiple of 4 + 1 (e.g. 81, 85, 89, 93 ).
This is required because WAN Video only processes frame batches in that pattern.

This is relevant for Frame Load Cap and Frames per Iteration, as mismatched values can cause glitchy frames.

nodes.title: Quick Guide
widgets_values:
## How to Use

Set up everything in the *Input Video & Settings* section.

### Target Resolution

Set the target resolution width and height.

### Enable for High Quality

Enabling this sets the steps of the sampler. False is normal quality with 1 step, and True is high quality with 2 steps, but takes longer to generate.

### Creativity

Adjusts the shift value to manipulate the sigma for the scheduler. A lower value adheres more to the source and is less generative, and a higher value is more generative and can create more details. High values can also create noise artifacts.

---

## Long Video

### Frames per Iteration

When the value is lower than your clip length, iterative sampling will activate itself automatically. Here you can control how many frames per iteration are sampled.

### Overlap Frames

Set the number of extra frames generated per iteration for blending each upscaled batch. More frames will take longer to generate, but fewer frames will make the stitched parts more obvious. 16 is a good middle ground.

### Save Image

Set Save Image Sequence to True if you have memory issues, e.g. with long 4K sequences. Activate it to save the upscaled output in between sampling iterations.
